CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 22, 1954, pg. 27, reads: "Uptown Little League Opener - A throng of some five hundred baseball fans saw the North Side Elks down the Pittsburgh Lions by a 1-0 score at Kennard Field, last Saturday, as Jack Bishop's homer decided the issue... Lower left: Jack Bishop of the North Side Elks, whose home run was the dramatic difference in a story book game... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Northside Elks Little League baseball player, no. 42 Jack Bishop, posed in batting stance during Uptown Little League opening day, Kennard Field
